1
00:00:03,827 --> 00:00:07,824
What we aspire for
is the ideal,

2
00:00:07,824 --> 00:00:12,499
when we imagine, 
envision, our counterpart.

3
00:00:12,669 --> 00:00:16,161
[Google God]

4
00:00:16,161 --> 00:00:18,994
It’s sometimes even 
expressed that way.

5
00:00:18,994 --> 00:00:24,798
People say, “Write here your ideal criteria
of who you envision to be your soulmate.”

6
00:00:24,798 --> 00:00:28,407
And they have something, 
“Well, it’ll be someone who’s like this,

7
00:00:28,407 --> 00:00:31,445
they’ll look like that,
their eyes might be like this” …

8
00:00:31,445 --> 00:00:37,327
they’re carrying some ideal
inside themselves

9
00:00:37,327 --> 00:00:42,341
about who that might be
or what they might be like.

10
00:00:42,341 --> 00:00:47,204
But what I mean 
to suggest here is

11
00:00:47,204 --> 00:00:57,494
to equate the ideal with the very
Absolute Personality of Godhead;

12
00:00:57,984 --> 00:01:04,921
that really if we search that ideal,
its extreme, we could refine it,

13
00:01:04,921 --> 00:01:09,053
refine our search criteria.

14
00:01:09,053 --> 00:01:13,610
If we could refine our search criteria
to the infinite degree,

15
00:01:13,610 --> 00:01:16,863
it will lead us to the Infinite.

16
00:01:16,863 --> 00:01:20,701
The Infinite Source of all love,
beauty, charm, sweetness,

17
00:01:20,701 --> 00:01:23,885
and all possible relationships.

